ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: I feel tense or 'wound up'...
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 1 = From time to time, occasionally; 2 = A lot of the time; 3 = Most of the time

ElementDescription: I still enjoy the things I used to enjoy
Notes: 0 = Definitely as much; 1 = Not quite so much; 2 = Only a little; 3 = Hardly at all

ElementDescription: I get a sort of frightened feeling as if something awful is about to happen
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 1 = A little, but it doesn't worry me; 2 = Yes, but not too badly; 3 = Very definitely and quite badly

ElementDescription: I can laugh and see the funny side of things
Notes: 0 = As much as I always could; 1 = Not quite so much now; 2 = Definitely not so much now; 3 = Not at all

ElementDescription: Worrying thoughts go through my mind
Notes: 0 = Only occasionally; 1 = From time to time, but not too often; 2 = A lot of the time; 3 = A great deal of time

ElementDescription: I feel cheerful
Notes: 0 = Most of the time; 1 = Sometimes; 2 = Not often; 3 = Not at all

ElementDescription: I can sit at ease and feel relaxed
Notes: 0 = Definitely; 1 = Usually; 2 = Not often; 3 = Not at all

ElementDescription: I feel as if I am slowed down
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 1 = Sometimes; 2 = Very often; 3 = Nearly all the time

ElementDescription: I get a sort of frightened feeling like 'butterflies' in the stomach
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 1 = Occationally; 2 = Quite often; 3 = Very often

ElementDescription: I have lost interest in my appearance
Notes: 0 = I take just as much care as ever; 1 = I may not take quite as much care; 2 = I don't take as much care as I should; 3 = Definitely

ElementDescription: I feel restless as if I have to be on the move
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 1 = Not very much; 2 = Quite a lot; 3 = Very much indeed

ElementDescription: I look forward with enjoyment to things
Notes: 0 = As much as I ever did; 1 = Rather less than I used to; 2 = Definitely less than I used to; 3 = Hardly at all

ElementDescription: I get sudden feelings of panic
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 1 = Not very often; 2 = Quite often; 3 = Very often indeed

ElementDescription: I can enjoy a good book or radio or TV program
Notes: 0 = Often; 1 = Sometimes; 2 = Not often; 3 = Very seldom

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime
